24 7-4-401. Document Validity Division.
25 (a) There is created within the office of the Secretary of State the
26 Document Validity Division.
27 (b) The Secretary of State may designate members of his or her staff
28 as record validity investigators, who shall investigate documents and
29 activities related to the validity and truthfulness of records submitted to
30 the office of the Secretary of State under Arkansas Code, Title 7, Chapters 5
31 or 9.
32 (c) The Document Validity Division shall be a law enforcement agency
33 of the office of the Secretary of State appointed by the Secretary of State
34 from his or her employees to investigate the validity of documents filed with
35 the Secretary of State under Arkansas Code, Title 7, Chapters 5 or 9.
