1 7-4-402. Investigations.
2 (a) The Secretary of State or a document validity investigator may
3 conduct an investigation to determine whether a document submitted to the
4 Secretary of State under Arkansas Code, Title 7, Chapters 5 or 9, is false or
5 fraudulent.
6 (b) An investigation under this subchapter may include without
7 limitation:
8 (1) Administering oaths;
9 (2) Issuing subpoenas;
10 (3) Compelling witness attendance;
11 (4) Collecting evidence; and
12 (5) Requiring the production of any books, papers,
13 correspondence, memorandum, agreements, or other documents or records that
14 are relevant or material to the inquiry.
15 (c) If an individual fails to comply with a subpoena request issued by
16 the Secretary of State or a document validity investigator under subsection
17 (b) of this section, the Secretary of State may request an order from a court
18 of appropriate jurisdiction to enforce the subpoena.
19 (d) A document determined by the division to contain fraud or falsity
20 by a preponderance of the evidence shall be declared null and void for any
21 legal purpose overseen by the Secretary of State.
22 (e) The division may refer any findings of fraud or falsity under this
23 subchapter to the Attorney General's office for further investigation and
24 action.
